## INSTALLATION
1) If using btrfs, edit your fstab to mount the btrfs partition you want to backup.
(If you choose a mount point different than /mnt/vol edit /etc/make-snapshots-target.conf to match.)
2) Build and install the package.
3) Enable the appropriate service:
  systemctl enable mk-btrfs-snapshots
  systemctl enable mk-lvm-snapshots
4) Edit /boot/grub/make-snapshots.cfg and edit /boot/grub/custom.cfg to source
/boot/grub/make-snapshots.cfg.
